Plan and actions taken
- Phase 1: Ran the CI compilation check (run_github_action) to see current compilation status.
- Found a single compilation error in IndexCompleteCriterion: it called context.addWarning(...), but CriterionEntityEvaluationContext does not expose addWarning().
- Applied an allowed fix (only changed files under src/main/java/com/java_template/application) to remove the invalid call and use a supported approach (logged a warning).
- Re-ran the CI compilation check to verify the fix.

What I changed
- Modified: src/main/java/com/java_template/application/criterion/IndexCompleteCriterion.java
  - Problem: used context.addWarning("...") where CriterionEntityEvaluationContext<T> has no addWarning method.
  - Fix: replaced the unsupported context.addWarning(...) call with a logger.warn(...) call so the missing-operation no longer breaks compilation.
  - Note: change is limited to the permitted directory and only that file was changed.

Run counts (CRITICAL)
- run_github_action calls used: 2 (≤ allowed maximum 3)

