Notes and rationale
- The compilation failure was due to invoking a nonexistent API on the evaluation context. Because I was constrained to edit only files under src/main/java/com/java_template/application, I fixed the criterion implementation to avoid calling the missing method.
- I used logger.warn(...) to surface the warning information. If the intended behavior is to attach warnings to the CriterionResponse, a proper API would be needed in the serializer/context; that requires edits outside the allowed scope or changes in shared libraries. Logging is safe and keeps compilation and behavior intact.

If you want next steps
- If you prefer warnings to be attached to the criterion response rather than merely logged, we should:
  - Add a method for attaching warnings to the CriterionEntityEvaluationContext and implement it in the serializer, OR
  - Use the CriterionSerializer/EvaluationChain API to attach warnings via ReasonAttachmentStrategy (but that requires changes to how validateEntity returns outcomes or uses the serializer chain).
- I can implement one of those if you permit edits outside the current limited set (or if you allow changes in the common serializer classes).

Summary
- I called run_github_action twice.
- Applied a minimal permitted fix to IndexCompleteCriterion.java in src/main/java/com/java_template/application.
- The project now compiles successfully (CI build succeeded).